## F. Mise à jour `pf.conf` sur OpenBSD

**Bug critique évité** : la macro `direct_net` (déclarée en phase 05) ne doit pas être confondue avec `dir_net` (qui n’existe pas et ferait planter le ruleset).

**Bug critique d’ordre** : le `pass in quick on $wan_if proto udp port 51820` doit venir AVANT le `block in quick on $wan_if`, sinon le block matche en premier (à cause du `quick`) et le pass n’est jamais évalué.

Sauvegarder l’actuel :

```
doas cp /etc/pf.conf /etc/pf.conf.phase05
```

Remplacer `/etc/pf.conf` :

```
doas vim /etc/pf.conf
```

Contenu complet à coller (`:set paste` puis `i` puis coller, `Esc :wq`) :

```
# /etc/pf.conf — phase 06 (WG inbound + Mullvad multihop préservé)

# === Macros ===
wan_if     = "vio0"
vpn_if     = "vio1"
dir_if     = "vio2"
wg_if      = "wg0"
wg_in      = "wg2"

vpn_net    = "10.0.10.0/24"
direct_net = "10.0.20.0/24"
wg_in_net  = "10.99.0.0/24"

wg_local    = "10.71.182.204"
wg_endpoint = "141.98.253.165"

void_ip    = "192.168.100.1"
wg_in_port = "51820"

# === Options ===
set skip on lo
set block-policy return
set loginterface $wan_if

# === Normalisation ===
match in all scrub (no-df random-id max-mss 1200)

# === Translation (NAT) ===
match out on $wg_if  inet from $vpn_net    to any nat-to ($wg_if:0)
match out on $wg_if  inet from (self)      to 10.64.0.1 nat-to ($wg_if:0)
match out on $wan_if inet from $direct_net to any nat-to ($wan_if:0)
match out on $wan_if inet from (self)      to any nat-to ($wan_if:0)

# === Politique par défaut ===
block drop log all

# === Sorties autorisées du router lui-même ===
pass out quick inet keep state

# === Anti-fuite VPN (kill-switch fail-closed) ===
block return out quick on $wan_if inet from $vpn_net to any

# === DNS du router vers Mullvad via wg0 ===
pass out on $wg_if inet from (self) to 10.64.0.1 keep state

# === DHCP serveur (vpn_net et direct_net) ===
pass in quick on { $vpn_if $dir_if } inet proto udp from any port 68 to port 67 keep state

# === WAN inbound : tout bloquer SAUF wg2 inbound ===
# IMPORTANT : pass UDP 51820 AVANT le block in
pass in quick on $wan_if inet proto udp to ($wan_if) port $wg_in_port keep state
block in quick on $wan_if

# === Services internes (br-vpn, br-direct) ===
pass in quick on $vpn_if inet proto tcp from $vpn_net    to ($vpn_if) port 22 keep state
pass in quick on $dir_if inet proto tcp from $direct_net to ($dir_if) port 22 keep state

pass in quick on $vpn_if inet proto { tcp udp } from $vpn_net    to ($vpn_if) port 53 keep state
pass in quick on $dir_if inet proto { tcp udp } from $direct_net to ($dir_if) port 53 keep state

pass in quick on $vpn_if inet proto icmp icmp-type echoreq keep state
pass in quick on $dir_if inet proto icmp icmp-type echoreq keep state

# === Tunnel WG inbound (wg2) ===
# SSH vers le router via tunnel
pass in quick on $wg_in inet proto tcp from $wg_in_net to ($wg_in) port 22 keep state

# ICMP depuis tunnel
pass in quick on $wg_in inet proto icmp from $wg_in_net icmp-type echoreq keep state

# Forward depuis tunnel vers ressources internes
pass in quick on $wg_in inet proto tcp from $wg_in_net to $void_ip port 22 keep state
pass in quick on $wg_in inet proto tcp from $wg_in_net to $vpn_net    port 22 keep state
pass in quick on $wg_in inet proto tcp from $wg_in_net to $direct_net port 22 keep state

pass in quick on $wg_in inet proto icmp from $wg_in_net to { $vpn_net $direct_net $void_ip } keep state

# === Sortie Internet pour les bridges ===
pass in quick on $vpn_if inet from $vpn_net    keep state
pass in quick on $dir_if inet from $direct_net keep state

# === Isolation inter-bridges ===
block drop quick on $vpn_if inet from $vpn_net    to $direct_net
block drop quick on $dir_if inet from $direct_net to $vpn_net
